description:
&lt;p&gt;Interested in joining an excellent team?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so a fantastic opportunity has arisen for an experienced or newly qualified Registered Nurse to join the Emergency Assessment Unit (EAU). EAU is a 40 bedded Unit which specialises in prioritising and delivering treatment and care to stabilise acutely ill patients prior to discharging them home in a safe, prompt and timely manner, or enabling transfer to the appropriate ward for the patient to receive ongoing care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although EAU is a very busy and demanding unit, it offers a wide variety of acute medical conditions across all ages within adult nursing. The Unit is fully supported by all members of the multi-disciplinary team to deliver outstanding care at all times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer an excellent in house training package with full individualised professional development plans that continue to grow throughout employment, including venipuncture, cannulation, and supervisor for students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EAU is a very friendly, supportive and fun team who takes care of each other and endeavors to build relationships with colleagues by attending regular social events.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Julie Goward, Department Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;julie.goward@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jo Henson (Clinical Educator) on 01623 622515 ext 6081 or email Jo.Henson@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
